            An unweighted GPA measures academic achievement on a standard 0 to 4.0 scale regardless of class difficulty. A weighted GPA accounts for course rigor by adding extra points (typically +0.5 for Honors and +1.0 for AP or IB courses), resulting in scores that can exceed 4.0.
          </div>
        </details>
      
        <details class="bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between font-sans font-semibold text-sm text-ink list-none hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-colors select-none">
